description: Gets the console output for the specified instance. For Linux instances, the instance console output displays the exact console output that would normally be displayed on a physical monitor attached to a computer. For Windows instances, the instance console output includes the last three system event log errors. For more information, see Instance console output in the Amazon EC2 User Guide.

parameters.name: Latest
parameters.description: When enabled, retrieves the latest console output for the instance. Default: disabled ( false)

nested_items.name: Timestamp
nested_items.description: The time at which the output was last updated.

nested_items.name: Output
nested_items.description: The console output, base64-encoded. If you are using a command line tool, the tool decodes the output for you.
